Perfect! I've built a **terminal-based Pomodoro timer** with full session tracking and statistics.

**What's been implemented:**
- ✅ 25-min focus sessions & 5-min breaks with live countdown
- ✅ Color-coded terminal UI with emojis
- ✅ Session tracking saved to `~/.pomodoro_data.json`
- ✅ Statistics command showing today/week/all-time sessions
- ✅ Pause/skip/quit controls
- ✅ Long breaks after 4 sessions
- ✅ Audio notifications on completion

**Try it:**
```bash
./pomodoro.py        # Start timer
./pomodoro.py stats  # View statistics
```

The timer is ready to use for productivity tracking!
